{
  "doc_id": "61196",
  "text": "Bartz et al. [CITATION_1] presented an solution which utilize a STN [CITATION_2] to circularly attend to each word in the input image, and then recognize them separately. The united network is trained in a weakly-supervised manner that no word bounding box labels are used. Li an encoder-decoder based text recognition model and make up their text spotting system. Lui et al. [CITATION_3] , Busta et al. [CITATION_4] and He et al. [CITATION_5] developed a unified text detection and recognition systems with a very similar overall architecture which consist of a detection branch and a recognition branch. Liu et al. [CITATION_6] and Busta et al. [CITATION_7] adopt EAST [CITATION_8] and YOLOv2 [CITATION_9] as their detection branch respectively, and have a similar text recognition branch in which text proposals are mapped into fixed height tensor by bilinear sampling and then transcribe in to strings by a CTC-based recognition module. He et al. [CITATION_10] also adopted EAST [CITATION_11] to generate text proposals, and they introduced character spatial information as explicit supervision in the attentionbased recognition branch.",
